An open curly brace should be located at the end of a line
Why is this an issue? Shared naming conventions allow teams to collaborate effectively. This rule raises an issue when an open curly brace is not placed at the end of a line of code. 
### Noncompliant
if(condition)
{
  doSomething();
}
 
### Compliant
if(condition) {
  doSomething();
}
 Exceptions When blocks are inlined (left and right curly braces on the same line), no issue is triggered. if(condition) {doSomething();}
### Noncompliant
{{BUGGY}}
